{"_id":"69VAtARVm5lT9Plg","name":"Magic User Spells","content":"<h1>Magic User Spells</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Unlike clerical and druidic spells, magic user spells (also known as Arcane spells in the OSRIC system) do not require a holy symbol or mistletoe as material components.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"276a92e4ddaa56193ea422df6847f2b16f2074e0","sourceId":"JournalEntry.69VAtARVm5lT9Plg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7k8wp5wanki","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Magic User Spells","color":"#000000","sort":191}}}
{"_id":"6AcwMe7BLWUtxWCc","name":"Create Food and Water","content":"<h1>Create Food and Water</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Clerical Transmutation/Alteration</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Cleric 3</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>10-ft</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Instantaneous (permanent)</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>A day's ration per caster level</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 turn</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tCreate Food and Water\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Upon completion of the ritual words of this spell, food and/ or water will appear from thin air. A caster of fifth level can conjure up enough food and water to sustain a person or even a horse for five full days. The volume of food and water produced by the spell is approximately one cubic-ft per level of the caster.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"92894b784a7f309c31e9fbefe6db15af6a651da2","sourceId":"JournalEntry.6AcwMe7BLWUtxWCc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_65r8ksx2p43","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Cleric Spells","color":"#000000","sort":50}}}
{"_id":"6m02Job4MpSK9v7h","name":"Colour Spray","content":"<h1>Colour Spray</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Phantasmal Transmutation/Alteration</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Illusionist 1</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>0</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 segment</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Cone, 5-ft wide at origin, 45% arc, 10-ft/level long</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S,M</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 segment</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>See below</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tColour Spray\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>The caster fans out his or her fingers, and a sheet of unearthly-coloured light springs forth. <b>[[/roll 1d6]] creatures caught within the light may be affected, </b>and <u>the spell can only affect 1 hit die of creatures per caster level. </u><b>Creatures with HD equal to or less than the caster's are rendered unconscious by the burst of colours. If the creature's hit dice exceed the caster's by 1-2, the creature is blinded for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds. If the creature has 3+ hit dice in excess of the caster's, it is merely stunned for [[/roll 2d4]] segments. </b><u>Any creature with hit dice exceeding the caster's (and creatures or 6+ HD regardless of the caster's level) are entitled to a saving throw.</u></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"95103dc19e873e86d693d83a02fe3105890f7a09","sourceId":"JournalEntry.6m02Job4MpSK9v7h"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7fkpa5jvvmt","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Illusionist Spells","color":"#000000","sort":395}}}
{"_id":"6uW25CnJ9RB3KPjg","name":"Detect Evil (Reversible)","content":"<h1>Detect Evil (Reversible)</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Arcane Divination</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Magic user 2</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Caster</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>5 rounds/level</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Path 10-ft wide, 60-ft long</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>2 segments</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tDetect Evil\n\t\t\t\t\t\tDetect Good\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This spell allows the magic user to detect emanations of evil (or good, in the case of the spell's reverse) within the spell's area of effect, a beam-like pathway. <b>The spell detects evil, not danger, so it will be useless to discover such things as a mindless trap or a poisoned wineglass. Neither will it detect a cursed item unless the nature of the curse is such that the cursed item becomes inherently evil.</b></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"0f53a621e9c23dc2bfd8a0feb289a2cb1c4d5d82","sourceId":"JournalEntry.7Vv3boqSst1uNUVD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7k8wp5wanki","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Magic User Spells","color":"#000000","sort":223}}}
{"_id":"6w38kB7V7UJm7eWP","name":"Dispel Illusion","content":"<h1>Dispel Illusion</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Phantasmal Abjuration</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Illusionist 3</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>10-ft/level</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Instantaneous</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>One illusion</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>3 segments</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tDispel Illusion\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>This spell automatically dispels phantasmal forces cast by non-illusionists. </b>All other illusion spells are treated as if this spell were a <i>dispel magic </i>(i.e., with a 50% base chance to dispel, adjusted up or down by 2% or 5% respectively, based on relative caster levels).</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"e0ab795ee6ce218f2b4392e4851ae2e77596b660","sourceId":"JournalEntry.6w38kB7V7UJm7eWP"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7fkpa5jvvmt","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Illusionist Spells","color":"#000000","sort":409}}}
{"_id":"71riAMhpAUdUjtoB","name":"Combat Modifiers","content":"<h1>Combat Modifiers</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>Concealment: </b>Concealment is anything that obscures an opponent's vision, such as tree limbs or smoke, but does not physically block incoming attacks (which would be considered Cover rather than Concealment; see below). The GM must decide whether the defender is about a quarter (-1 to AC), half (-2 to AC), three-quarters (-3 to AC), or nine tenths (-4 to AC) concealed.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>Cover: </b>Cover is protection behind something that can actually block incoming attacks, such as a wall or arrow slit. Cover bonuses are as follows:</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>25% cover: -2 AC</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>50% cover: -4 AC</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>75% cover: -7 AC</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>90% cover: -10 AC</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>An attack from the unshielded flank denies the target any defensive advantages from a shield. An attack from the rear flank negates the defensive value of the shield and also negates any dexterity bonus.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>Invisible opponent: </b>An invisible opponent can only be attacked if the general location is known, and the attack is at -4 to hit. If an opponent is invisible to the attacker, he or she cannot be attacked from behind (or from the flank). Note that more powerful monsters (those with sensitive smell or hearing, or more than six hit dice) will frequently be able to detect invisible opponents; the GM should determine the chance of this according to the creature concerned and the situation. Powerful magical monsters, or those with more than 11 hit dice, will almost always be able to see invisible creatures normally.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>Prone Opponent: </b>Attacks against a prone opponent negate the benefit of a shield, negate dexterity bonuses, and are made at +4 to hit.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>Rear Attack: </b>An attack from directly behind an opponent negates the benefit of a shield, negates dexterity bonuses, and is made at +2 to hit.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>Sleeping Opponent: </b>Sleeping opponents (natural sleep, not magical sleep) may be attacked with the same chance to kill as if the attacker were an assassin. The effect of magical sleep is described under the entry for the sleep spell.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>Stunned Opponent: </b>A stunned opponent receives no shield or dexterity bonus, and may be attacked at +4.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>Two-Weapon Fighting: </b>If a character desires to fight with one weapon in each hand, the off-hand weapon must be either a dagger or a hand axe. The weapon in the primary hand attacks with a -2 modifier, and the off-hand weapon attacks at -4. The character's dexterity bonus (or penalty) for missile weapons is added to both attacks. Thus, a character with a dexterity of 3 would be attacking at -5/-7. However, although penalties can be offset, this rule can never result in a bonus to attacks! The off-hand weapon cannot be used to affect parrying.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"b68df996f5c0d7309de24c1326ee3d42e9cdb73f","sourceId":"JournalEntry.71riAMhpAUdUjtoB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bgxgvfs1b8","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 3: How to Play#/CF_SEP/COMBAT","color":"#000000","sort":462}}}
{"_id":"7JiZMh0N1ZycyxbJ","name":"Spider Climb","content":"<h1>Spider Climb</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Arcane Transmutation/Alteration</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Magic user 1</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Touch</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 round+1 round/ evel</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>One creature</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S,M</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 segment</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSpider Climb\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>When the magic user casts this spell, <b>the recipient's bare hands and feet become sticky enough to allow him or her to climb walls and even crawl along a ceiling. </b>The movement rate for such climbing is 30-ft per round. <u>The subject of this spell will find it difficult to employ tools or handle small objects with precision while the spell is in effect.</u></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"7c12905fdcdac396d31a1ff3c92b9595705631d1","sourceId":"JournalEntry.7JiZMh0N1ZycyxbJ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7k8wp5wanki","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Magic User Spells","color":"#000000","sort":354}}}
{"_id":"7RfDlS2OjS1WbNX4","name":"Know Alignment (Reversible)","content":"<h1>Know Alignment (Reversible)</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Clerical Divination</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Cleric 2</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Touch</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 turn</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 creature/round</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 round</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tKnow Alignment\n\t\t\t\t\t\tUndetectable Alignment\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>All creatures are surrounded by an aura that can indicate their alignment, and this spell allows the caster to perceive and read such auras. The auras of up to ten creatures may be examined by use of the spell, and the cleric will be able to identify the exact alignment of each. The reverse of the spell obscures alignment (even against the use of this spell) with respect to one creature for a period of 1 turn, two people for a period of 5 rounds, and so on.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"3555ee7a7a25c5e7bb2d5a588889e77546ec9651","sourceId":"JournalEntry.7RfDlS2OjS1WbNX4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_65r8ksx2p43","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Cleric Spells","color":"#000000","sort":76}}}
{"_id":"7bfBZsZH3Ti6CAsp","name":"Quest","content":"<h1>Quest</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Clerical Enchantment/Charm</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Cleric 5</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>60-ft</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>See below</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>One creature</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S,M</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>8 segments</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Negates</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tQuest\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>By means of a <i>quest </i>spell, the cleric enslaves the subject into fulfilling a task the cleric sets, forcing him or her to perform the task and return to the cleric with proof of its completion. <b>If the enchanted creature does not properly follow the letter and spirit of the quest, it will suffer a cumulative penalty of -1 to all saving throw rolls for each day the quest is neglected </b>. This penalty, which is itself in the nature of a curse, remains with the creature until the quest is completed or the curse is removed by the caster or by some other agency. Possible objectives for a quest are legion; they might include finding and bringing some valuable item to the cleric, capturing a castle, slaying a monster, or any number of other tasks.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"d5022431414cde038357fbeafccb4b25b3babbc2","sourceId":"JournalEntry.7bfBZsZH3Ti6CAsp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_65r8ksx2p43","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Cleric Spells","color":"#000000","sort":87}}}
{"_id":"82gxXnoLp58w6a60","name":"Maze","content":"<h1>Maze</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Phantasmal Conjuration/Summoning</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Illusionist 5</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>5-ft/level</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>See below</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>One creature</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>5 segments</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tMaze\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Other than as may be noted above, this spell is identical to the magic user spell of the same name.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"8c8b6e76434ae25aaf0c445553254cc8ea762171","sourceId":"JournalEntry.kNWWx7sxOjfVKnLE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7fkpa5jvvmt","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Illusionist Spells","color":"#000000","sort":427}}}
{"_id":"86p3ezAPW1Q867Jj","name":"Cure Light Wounds (Reversible)","content":"<h1>Cure Light Wounds (Reversible)</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Druidic Necromancy</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Druid 2</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Touch</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Instantaneous (permanent)</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Creature touched</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S,M</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>4 segments</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None (neg.)</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tCure Light Wounds\n\t\t\t\t\t\tCause Light Wounds\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>The druidic cure light wounds is, except as described above, identical to the clerical spell of the same name.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"e8eb38ddbbb96f6269f1b92768e7c7c246f665a9","sourceId":"JournalEntry.Vy5PVWVfmne8rXYI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w788fmzkfq","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Druid Spells","color":"#000000","sort":137}}}
{"_id":"8G08R5TB3lsLMomO","name":"Hallucinatory Terrain","content":"<h1>Hallucinatory Terrain</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Phantasmal Illusion</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Illusionist 3</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>20-ft+20-ft/level</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>See below</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>40-ft40-ft square area+10-ft square/level</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S,M</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>5 rounds</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tHallucinatory Terrain\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Except as may be noted above, this spell is identical to the magic user spell of the same name.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"17986e619e6f4a977fe424c3fc8ad4ef4bc337ad","sourceId":"JournalEntry.K5v2YgxWRYdtUDMe"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7fkpa5jvvmt","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Illusionist Spells","color":"#000000","sort":414}}}
{"_id":"8Jt9pAstualk5l99","name":"Summon Insects","content":"<h1>Summon Insects</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<i>Druidic Conjuration/Summoning</i>\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tbody><tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Level:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Druid 3</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Range:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>30-ft</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Duration:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 round/caster level</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Area of Effect:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>See below</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Components:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>V,S,M</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Casting Time:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>1 round</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>Saving Throw:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td>None</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody></table>\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\tSummon Insects\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>When the druid completes the intonations and gestures of this spell, a swarm of insects appears from nearby or from the thin air to attack the druid's enemies. <b>There is a 70% chance that the swarm will be composed of flying insects, 30% chance that the insects will be ants or other non-airborne biting vermin. </b>A flying swarm can move tremendously fast, but a crawling swarm is limited to movement of 12-ft/round. <b>In either case, the insects automatically inflict 2 hp damage per round against their target, and the unfortunate victim will be so thickly covered as to be incapable of any action, including movement. </b>The druid may redirect the swarm to attack another opponent, but the command will cause 1 round of confusion within the swarm as it reorients itself toward the new target.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I0IQ9ef7ZhLd66iw":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"hash":"b3d0eb789c87d2ecb3fc18d4b89d9ba446f7ffb9","sourceId":"JournalEntry.8Jt9pAstualk5l99"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w788fmzkfq","path":"OSRIC-PC#/CF_SEP/Chapter 2: Spells#/CF_SEP/Druid Spells","color":"#000000","sort":179}}}
